explanation: [0-0] A hydraulic press appears in the frame, with round metal plates installed at both the top and bottom. Between the metal plates, four brightly colored sponges are stacked vertically, from top to bottom: yellow, green, blue, and red. The background is a gray-green wall with a red lightning bolt symbol on the right.

[0-3] Next, the hydraulic press lowers, compressing the sponges and squeezing out the water inside them, which spills onto a gray platform. Subsequently, the dehydrated sponges emerge from beneath the metal plate.

[3-11] Then, a bunch of lit tea lights are closely arranged on the lower metal plate. The hydraulic press descends onto the tea lights, extinguishing the flames and causing white smoke to emanate. The press crushes the tea lights, and melted wax overflows from the edges. Next, four pieces of colored clay are placed in pairs on the lower metal plate, purple, pink, green, and red, respectively. The hydraulic press lowers, flattening the clay pieces and causing them to ooze out from between the metal plates. Afterwards, two heart-shaped wax blocks and a wax block with a white hexagonal star in the center are placed on the lower metal plate. The heart-shaped wax blocks are green and blue, respectively. The hydraulic press lowers, flattening the wax blocks and causing them to spill out from between the metal plates. Finally, there is a colorful plasticine wrapped in black metal mesh. The hydraulic press lowers, squeezing the plasticine out of the gaps in the metal mesh, forming colorful strips.
